# UI/UX Pro Max Guidelines

## Priority 1: Accessibility (CRITICAL)
- Color contrast minimum 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text
- Visible focus rings on interactive elements (2-4px)
- Alt text for meaningful images
- Color must not be the only indicator (add icon/text)

## Priority 2: Touch & Interaction (CRITICAL)
- Min touch target 44x44px (iOS) / 48x48dp (Android)
- Min 8px spacing between touch targets
- Use click/tap for primary interactions, don't rely on hover alone
- Disable button during async; show spinner/progress
- `touch-action: manipulation` to reduce 300ms delay
- Visual feedback on press within 100ms

## Priority 3: Performance (HIGH)
- WebP/AVIF images, lazy load non-critical
- Reserve space for async content (CLS < 0.1)
- Skeleton screens instead of long spinners
- Debounce/throttle high-frequency events

## Priority 4: Style (HIGH)
- Consistent style across all pages
- SVG icons, not emojis
- One primary CTA per screen
- Consistent elevation/shadow scale
- Design light/dark variants together

## Priority 5: Layout (HIGH)
- Mobile-first breakpoints (375/768/1024/1440)
- 4pt/8dp spacing system
- No horizontal scroll on mobile
- Consistent max-width on desktop

## Priority 6: Typography & Color (MEDIUM)
- Base 16px, line-height 1.5-1.75
- Semantic color tokens, not raw hex in components
- Font-weight hierarchy: Bold(600-700) headings, Regular(400) body
- Dark mode: desaturated/lighter tonal variants

## Priority 7: Animation (MEDIUM)
- Duration 150-300ms for micro-interactions
- Use transform/opacity only; avoid animating width/height
- ease-out for entering, ease-in for exiting
- Exit animations shorter than enter (~60-70%)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Priority 8: Forms (MEDIUM)
- Visible label per input (not placeholder-only)
- Error placement below the related field
- Disabled elements: reduced opacity (0.38-0.5)
- Inline validation on blur, not keystroke

## Priority 9: Navigation (HIGH)
- Current location visually highlighted
- Modals must offer clear close affordance
- Back navigation preserves scroll/state
